see both the tables and the columns that are there.

00:16:09.520 --> 00:16:12.320
So the tips that we have here are similar.

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:20.400
It's worth it to learn a little bit of SQL, because it turns out that when we know a little

00:16:20.400 --> 00:16:24.400
bit of what's going on under the hood, it helps us understand it's not magic and to

00:16:25.039 --> 00:16:27.039
solve problems that we may run into.

00:16:28.080 --> 00:16:30.239
And again, we get these kind of subtleties here.

00:16:31.039 --> 00:16:35.119
That connections pane that I showed you also works with DuckDB.

00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:38.320
So DuckDB, there's overlap in these technologies.

00:16:38.320 --> 00:16:42.000
Like, they're not all different from each other, but rather fairly similar.

